    note right of DefaultDefault
        States encode two orthogonal dimensions:
        Tiling: Default=not-explicit, TilingSet=explicit-no-params, TilingParamsSet=explicit-params-set
        Compression: Default=not-explicit, ComprSet=explicit-no-type, ComprTypeSet=explicit-type-set
        setTilingMode/setCompressionMode are value-dependent (mode parameter determines target).
        DFA conservatively transitions to Explicit states; false negatives accepted for non-EXPLICIT values.
        getTileWidth/Height/GridX/GridY require tiling params to be set (TilingParamsSet states only).
        setCompressionQuality, getCompressionQuality, getBitRate, etc. require type set (ComprTypeSet states only).
    end note
